            <thetext>The qx.ui.splitpane.SplitPane uses cursor styles &quot;row-resize&quot; and &quot;col-resize&quot; which are not supported in Opera (don&#39;t know about Safari). However, Opera supports &quot;n-resize&quot; and &quot;e-resize&quot;, which are also appropriate (in fact, these cursors do not point to north or east only, but in both vertical or horizontal directions).

Is there a way to use the &quot;col-resize&quot; and &quot;row-resize&quot; cursors in FF and IE, and &quot;n-resize&quot; and &quot;e-resize&quot; in Opera (and maybe Safari)? I&#39;d also like to do that in a custom widget. Maybe you could map the unsupported cursors to a best-fit under the hood?</thetext>
          </long_desc>
